Hi, this is Meryle, one of the people working with POV on this forum.  I work at the William Paterson University women's center and I have spent years hearing a lot of girls, women, and men talk about their lives.  I have learned a lot from all these conversations and from thinking more about my own life.  <br><br>
Meghan raised some really important questions about how we know what we want.  It is often very hard for girls -- for anyone who may have dreams that seem out of reach or that are different from what they HEAR other people saying is possible.  <br><br>
Sometimes girls (really women of all ages) come into the center whispering about a dream or feeling they have about their lives.  They are looking for a support from a place that is safe (and that won't laugh at their dreams).<br><br>
I know how much it matters to have people around that you can depend on to listen, be supportive, and help think of steps to get from where you are to where you want to go.<br><br>
I also know that at times in life it seems harder to dream than at other times.<br><br>
Even at these points, it helps to have people around who can listen and be there.<br><br>
I would love to know whether you feel you have a place to go and people to talk to or whether you feel your friends, family, teachers, etc are pushing you to compromise.<br><br>
Meryle   
